To simplify \((10 - \sqrt{75})/5\), note that \(\sqrt{75}=\sqrt{25\cdot3}=5\sqrt3\).  Hence

\[
\frac{10-\sqrt{75}}{5}
=\frac{10-5\sqrt3}{5}
=\frac{10}{5}-\frac{5\sqrt3}{5}
=2-\sqrt3.
\]

To simplify \((6 - \sqrt{45})/3\), note that \(\sqrt{45} = \sqrt{9\cdot5} = 3\sqrt5\).  Then

\[
\frac{6 - \sqrt{45}}{3}
=\frac{6 - 3\sqrt5}{3}
=\frac{6}{3}-\frac{3\sqrt5}{3}
=2-\sqrt5.
\]

To simplify the principal square root,

\[
\sqrt{\frac{25}{16}}
= \frac{\sqrt{25}}{\sqrt{16}}
= \frac{5}{4}.
\]

To simplify \(\sqrt{\tfrac{49}{81}}\), split the root over numerator and denominator:

\[
\sqrt{\frac{49}{81}}
=\frac{\sqrt{49}}{\sqrt{81}}
=\frac{7}{9}.
\]

First factor under the radical:

\[
\sqrt{\frac{24p^3}{49}}
=\frac{1}{7}\,\sqrt{24p^3}
=\frac{1}{7}\,\sqrt{24\;p^2\;p}
=\frac{p}{7}\,\sqrt{24p}.
\]

Since \(\sqrt{24}=2\sqrt6\), this becomes

\[
\frac{p}{7}\cdot2\sqrt{6p}
=\frac{2p\sqrt{6p}}{7}.
\]

First note that  
\[
\sqrt{\frac{48\,x^5}{100}}
=\sqrt{\frac{48}{100}}\;\sqrt{x^5}
=\frac{\sqrt{48}}{10}\;x^{5/2}
=\frac{4\sqrt3}{10}\;x^{5/2}
=\frac{2\sqrt3}{5}\;x^{5/2}.
\]  
Since \(x^{5/2}=x^2\sqrt{x}\), you can also write the answer as  
\[
\frac{2x^2\sqrt{3x}}{5}\,,
\]  
provided \(x\ge0\).
